What are the specific types of telescopes or cameras needed to observe the craters on the moon's surface? Can you provide a detailed list of the three features of the moon that can only be detected through specialized equipment, including the exact specifications of the necessary telescopes, cameras, and probes? Also, could you please provide the C++ code that can be used to analyze the data obtained from these instruments?
The Excel table below provides the required information:
| Feature      | Description                                                         | Equipment/Instrument                                                         |
|--------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Craters      | Bowl-shaped depressions on the moon's surface caused by meteor impacts | Reflecting telescopes with an aperture of at least 6 inches, such as the Celestron CPC Deluxe 1100 HD, Lunar Reconnaissance Orbiter Camera with a resolution of at least 50 meters |
| Rilles       | Narrow, winding depressions on the moon's surface caused by volcanic activity | Lunar Orbiter with a resolution of at least 1 meter, Lunar Reconnaissance Orbiter with a resolution of at least 50 meters |
| Lunar swirls | Bright, swirling patterns on the moon's surface caused by magnetic fields    | Lunar Prospector, Lunar Reconnaissance Orbiter with a resolution of at least 50 meters |
To analyze the data obtained from these instruments, you can use the following C++ code:
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>
using namespace std;
int main () {
  string line;
  ifstream myfile ("moon_data.txt");
  if (myfile.is_open())
  {
    while ( getline (myfile,line) )
    {
      cout << line << '\n';
    }
    myfile.close();
  }
  else cout << "Unable to open file"; 
  return 0;
} 
Please replace "moon_data.txt" with the name of the file that contains the data obtained from the instruments.

